{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Brazilian Fencing Confederation |abbrev = CBE |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Fencing]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[Brazil]] |founded = 1927 |aff = [[Fédération Internationale d'Escrime|FIE]] |affdate = |region = [[Pan American Fencing Confederation|PAFC]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil]] |location = |president = Gerli dos Santos |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |director = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = http://www.brasilesgrima.com.br/ |countryflag = Brazil }} The '''Brazilian Fencing Confederation''' ({{lang-pt|Confederação Brasileira de Esgrima}} ('''CBE''')) is the national organization responsible for managing and promoting the sport of [[fencing]] in [[Brazil]]. The CBE was founded in 1927 and is headquartered in [[Rio de Janeiro]].
The CBE is affiliated with the [[International Fencing Federation]]. Its president is Gerli dos Santos, and its vice president is Ricardo Machado Pacheco.
