{{Infobox organization | name = Davao Regional Football Association | image = Davao F.A..png | image_border = | size = 150 | caption = | abbreviation = DRFA | motto = | formation = | founder = | type = Football association | headquarters = | location = | region = [[Davao City]], [[Davao del Sur]] and [[Davao Oriental]] | coords = | membership = 22 clubs (2015) | leader_title = [[President]] | leader_name = Erwin Protacio | sec_gen = | parent_organization = [[Philippine Football Federation]] | website = }} The '''Davao Regional Football Association''' or '''DRFA''' is a [[Philippines|Filipino]] [[Association football|football]] association based in [[Davao City]]. It works under the [[Philippine Football Federation]] as provincial football association for [[Davao City]]. This scope was expanded by a mandate by the [[Philippine Football Federation]] allowing the DFA jurisdiction over clubs in [[Davao del Sur]] and [[Davao Oriental]]. The Davao FA sends a team to represent the region in the yearly [[PFF National Men's Club Championship]].
