The '''Mendiola Football Club 1991''' or '''Mendiola United FC''' is an [[association football]] club based in the [[Philippines]]. It was founded in 1991. It trains and enters teams in various age groups from the Youth level to the Senior level. It is one of the founding members of [[United Football League (Philippines)|United Football League]], which was last saw competing in the [[2009–10 United Football League (Philippines)|2009–10 season]].

At the [[2011 PFF National Men's Club Championship]], Mendiola played under the name Smart San Beda F.C. for sponsorship reasons.<ref>{{cite news|title=How Smart San Beda footballers relieve pain|url=http://www.philstar.com/health-and-family/772446/how-smart-san-beda-footballers-relieve-pain|accessdate=5 August 2015|publisher=The Philippine Star|date=31 January 2012}}</ref>
In 2012, the club resurgent by joining the [[2012–13 United Football Cup|2012–13 UFL Cup]] and defeating FC Masbate 4–0 in Stage 1.

